Pao suvattii, or Arrowhead puffer, is a species of pufferfish. It is a medium-sized pufferfish, reaching 11.5 cm (4.5 in) SL. It is also known as a Pignose Puffer or a Mekong Puffer. It is locally common in the Lower Mekong basin, and is exclusively a freshwater fish.The specific name honours Thai ichthyologist Chote Suvatti, former professor of Kasetsart University,  who collected the type specimen at Mekong.